{{Expand French|Bibliothèque universitaire des langues et civilisations|date=October 2017}}
[[File:BULAC, Paris.JPG|thumb|BULAC sign]]
The '''Bibliothèque universitaire des langues et civilisations''' (BULAC) is a major [[academic library]] located in [[Paris Rive Gauche]] and which has been open to the public since its 2011 opening. The library has a scope that includes  all languages and civilisations that are not those of the [[Western World]].<ref name="officialwebpresentation">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bulac.fr/la-bulac-en-bref/lessentiel/|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=L'essentiel}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.enssib.fr/breves/2011/09/19/un-nouveau-pole-des-langues-et-civilisations-tout-proche-de-la-bnf|language=French|publisher=École nationale supérieure des sciences de l'information et des bibliothèques|title=Un nouveau pôle des langues et civilisations tout proche de la BnF}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://helda.helsinki.fi/handle/10138/45364|language=English|publisher=University of Helsinki|title=BULAC Library two years after opening}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sorbonne.fr/etablissement/les-bibliotheques/bibliotheque-universitaire-des-langues-et-civilisations/|language=French|publisher=La Chancellerie des universités de Paris|title=Bibliothèque universitaire des Langues et Civilisations}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.evous.fr/BULAC-Bibliotheque-Universitaire-des-langues-et-civilisations,1174092.html |title=BULAC (Bibliothèque Universitaire des langues et civilisations)|author=Pauline |date=12 April 2012 |website= Evous |publisher= |access-date= 14 October 2017 |quote=|language=French}}</ref>. It provides more than one million documents written in all languages<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://library.ifla.org/887/|language=French|publisher=The International Federation of Library Associations|title=350 langues, 80 alphabets dans une seule bibliothèque… Défis et enjeux}}</ref>,  formed from the former collections of more than 20 libraries.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Lo |first1=Patrick|last2=KW Chiu |first2=Dickson|last3= Cho |first3= Allan |date=3 April 2017 |title=Inside the World's Major East Asian Collections: One Belt, One Road, and Beyond|url=https://books.google.co.nz/books?id=RJmpDQAAQBAJ |location= |publisher= [[Chandos Publishing]] |page=209 |isbn= 9780081021460 |author-link= }}</ref>

== Building ==

The construction of the building began in summer 2008. The architect is [[Yves Lion]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bulac.fr/pole/presentation/|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=Le Pôle des langues et civilisations}}</ref>. The library has five floors within the building, the public space is on three floors with 910 seats <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bulac.fr/uploads/media/BULAC-guide-du-lecteur-2011-12-02.pdf|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=Le guide du lecteur}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>.

The building is under the responsibility of the region [[Île-de-France]] which also provided two third of the financing, the [[France|French State]] provided the rest. The financing was about 80 millions euros)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bulac.fr/fileadmin/fichiers/direction/jpro2012/Synthese-chiffres-BULAC.pdf|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=Le projet BULAC en chiffre}}</ref>.

The operating cost is about 2.5 millions euros per year.

== Status ==

The BULAC is legally a [[:fr:groupement d'intérêt public]] made of the following institutions : 
*The French State ([[:fr:ministère de l'Enseignement supérieur et de la Recherche]]) ; 
*[[Institut national des langues et civilisations orientales]] (INALCO) ;
*[[École pratique des hautes études]] (EPHE) ;
*[[School for Advanced Studies in the Social Sciences]] (EHESS) ;
*[[École française d'Extrême-Orient]] ;
*[[Pantheon-Sorbonne University]] ;
*[[University of Paris III: Sorbonne Nouvelle]] ;
*[[Paris-Sorbonne University]] ;
*[[Paris Diderot University]] ;
*[[centre national de la recherche scientifique]] (CNRS).

The BULAC is administrated by a general assembly where the ministry has four representatives (two interested in higher education, two interested in research). The other preceding institutions have one representative each <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bulac.fr/la-bulac/le-gip-bulac/assemblee-generale/|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=L'assemblée général}}</ref>. A [[:fr:conseil scientifique]] made of french and foreign professors and researchers defines the general [[Collection Management Policy]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bulac.fr/la-bulac/le-gip-bulac/conseil-scientifique/|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=Le conseil scientifique}}</ref>.

; Direction

BULAC direction is made of a director, a vice-director and a scientific director<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bulac.fr/fileadmin/fichiers/direction/organigramme/BULAC-organigramme-2017-09-26.pdf|language=French|publisher=Official website of the BULAC|title=Organigramme de la BULAC|access-date=2017-12-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222053101/http://www.bulac.fr/fileadmin/fichiers/direction/organigramme/BULAC-organigramme-2017-09-26.pdf|archive-date=2017-12-22|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>.
* Director: [[:viaf:172730882|Marie-Lise Tsagouria]]
* Vice-director: Jean-François Chanal
* Scientific director: [[:viaf:316668672|Benjamin Guichard]] who took over from [[:viaf:76322035|Francis Richard]] in 2015

