'''Cayman Islands English''' is an English variety spoken in the [[Cayman Islands]]. While not much has been written on Cayman Islands English, according to one text, it "seems to have borrowed [[creole language|creole]] features similar to Jamaica and Central America without having undergone creolization".<ref>{{cite book|last=Holm|first=John A.|title=Pidgins and Creoles|volume=Volume 2, Reference Survey|year=1989|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-35940-5|pages=479–480|chapter=Cayman Islands|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PcD7p9y3EIcC&pg=PA405}}</ref> It is similar to [[Bay Islands English]].

