{{other uses|Orangism (disambiguation){{!}}Orangism}} '''Orangism''' was a political current in what is now [[Belgium]] that supported its inclusion in the short-lived [[United Kingdom of the Netherlands]] (1815&ndash;1830). After the secession of Belgium in 1830, Orangist sentiment in [[Flanders]] and [[Wallonia]] for a time sought a restoration of the United Kingdom of the Netherlands. It was a movement directed by [[William I of the Netherlands]] as part of his "Volhardingspolitiek" and containing most of the Belgian elites (nobility, industrials). Some of the most prominent Flemish Orangists were [[Jan Frans Willems]] and [[Hippolyte Metdepenningen]]. Although refusing to participate in parliamentary elections as they deemed Belgian national institutions as illegitimate, the Orangists did take part in local elections (province and municipal) from which they activated against the new Belgian state through political actions and an activist press. At least three Orangist coups were foiled during the 1830s. Although losing Dutch financial and political support after the [[Treaty of London (1839)|Treaty of London]] (1839) and William I's abdication (1840), the weakening Belgian Orangism survived well into the 1850s, strongly opposing the [[Belgian Revolution]] and rallying against independence.<ref>Els Witte, "Het verloren Koninkrijk", De Bezige Bij, Antwrpen, 2014, 688 p.</ref>
It was one inspiration for the later [[Greater Netherlands]] movement, although that movement was not all monarchist.
==Known Belgian Orangists==
===Present day=== * [[Louis Tobback]] (Socialist politician)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.besteburen.eu/nieuws/oranje-onder-brandpunt-bezoekt-louis-tobback-orangist-en-burgemeester-van-leuven|title=Oranje onder: Brandpunt bezoekt Louis Tobback, orangist en burgemeester van Leuven |publisher=besteburen.eu}}</ref> * [[Siegfried Bracke]] (Flemish nationalist politician, former journalist)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/nbna12072003_007|title=Ik ben al jaren overtuigd Groot-Nederlander|first=door Kris|last=VANDERHAEGEN|publisher=}}</ref> * {{Interlanguage link multi|Herman Balthazar|nl}} (Historian, professor, former governor of [[East Flanders]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://intervista.be/2013/03/01/herman-balthazar-ik-droom-soms-nog-dat-ik-een-weelderige-haardos-heb/|title=Herman Balthazar: ‘Ik droom soms nog dat ik een weelderige haardos heb’|first=Mikaël|last=Soinne|date=1 March 2013|publisher=}}</ref> * [[Geert van Istendael]] (Writer, poet, essayist)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://achillevandenbranden.blogspot.be/2010/03/mijn-nederland-geert-van-istendael.html|title=Achille [oude website]: Mijn Nederland - Geert van Istendael|publisher=}}</ref> * {{Interlanguage link multi|Bob Cools|nl}} (Socialist politician, former mayor of [[Antwerp]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20130426_00557973|title=‘Jammer dat de Nederlanden uiteenvielen’|first=Saskia|last=castelyns|publisher=}}</ref>
