{{Infobox Artifact
|name       = Rogozen Treasure
|image      = [[File:Rogozen.jpg|250px]]
|image_caption = A silver [[Patera|phiale]] with gold decoration depicting [[Auge]] and [[Heracles]].<ref>[http://archaeologyinbulgaria.com/2018/04/12/6-amazing-artifacts-with-ancient-greek-mythology-scenes-discovered-in-bulgaria/ 6 AMAZING ARTIFACTS WITH ANCIENT GREEK MYTHOLOGY SCENES DISCOVERED IN BULGARIA]</ref>
|material   = [[silver]]
|created    = 400 [[Anno Domini|B.C.]] - 300 [[Anno Domini|B.C.]]  
|discovered = 1985 at [[Rogozen]]
|location   = [[Vratsa Regional Historical Museum]]<br>[[National Historical Museum (Bulgaria)|National Historical Museum]], [[Sofia]]
}}
[[File:NHM-BG-photo4.JPG|thumb|250px|right|A goblet of the Rogozen treasure.]]
The '''Rogozen Treasure''' ({{lang-bg|Рогозенско съкровище}}), called the find of the century, is a Thracian treasure.{{sfn|Marazov|1989|page=12}}

== Discovery ==

It was discovered by chance in July 1985 by a tractor driver digging a well in his garden in the [[Bulgaria]]n village of [[Rogozen]].{{sfn|Marazov|1989|pages=11–12}}{{sfn|Eisenberg|1998|p=14}}

== Description ==

It consists of 165 receptacles, including 108 [[Phiale (libation vessel)|phiales]], 55 [[jug (container)|jug]]s and 3 [[goblet]]s.{{sfn|Marazov|1989|page=12}} The objects are silver with golden gilt on some of them with total weight of more than 20&nbsp;kg. The treasure is an invaluable source of information for the life of the [[Thracians]], due to the variety of motifs in the richly decorated objects. It is dated back to the 5th–4th centuries B.C.

==Honour==
[[Rogozen Island]] off [[Robert Island]], [[South Shetland Islands]] is named after the settlement of Rogozen in connection with the Rogozen Treasure.<ref>[https://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/display_name.cfm?gaz_id=136731 Rogozen Island] [https://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/ SCAR Composite Gazetteer of Antarctica]</ref>

